# Host-specific dashcam NFS coordinates for `task k8s:<env>:dashcam-pv`.
#
# Copy to `dashcam-nfs.local.env` (gitignored) and fill in your NAS export.
# The task sources these and synths the cluster-scoped dashcam PersistentVolume
# with them, applying it OUTSIDE Argo (the committed dist/ carries placeholders,
# so no host specifics live in git). Both prod and stage read NFS_PATH — the
# canonical regenerated _opt/clips export (e.g. the ADanaLife share's
# _opt/clips); one file serves both, the per-env PV name differs (config.py).
#
# Quote the values — the task sources this file with sh, so paths with spaces or
# an apostrophe (e.g. a NAS share like "Dana's Photos") need double quotes.
NFS_SERVER="<NFS server address>"
NFS_PATH="<export path>"

# Optional: point an individual env at a different export than the shared
# NFS_PATH — e.g. to let stage run ahead on a fresh corpus while prod stays put.
# Unset → that env uses NFS_PATH. After changing it, recreate that env's PV+PVC
# (NFS path is immutable on a bound PV) — see `task k8s:<env>:dashcam-pv`.
# STAGE_NFS_PATH="<stage-specific export>"
